article.headline: San Diego St. 71, Wyoming 60
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Billy White scored a career-high 24 points as he set a school shooting record to lead San Diego State to a 71-60 win over Wyoming on Saturday night. White broke the school record by making all 12 of his shots, each from right around the basket. White also had a career-high four blocked shots, including a spectacular block on Brandon Ewing in the second half. White capped off his night with a steal that led to his slam dunk off a lob pass from Richie Williams for a 66-49 lead with 2:50 left. San Diego State (18-6, 8-3 Mountain West) won its 10th consecutive home game. Ewing led Wyoming (14-10, 3-7) with 22 points and Afam Muojeke added 13.
